    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe following `minimal.lua` throws an error.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal test = false\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"ColorSchemePre\", {\r\n\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\ttest = true\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"UIEnter\", {\r\n\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\tpcall(vim.cmd.colorscheme, \"somecolorscheme\")\r\n\t\tif not test then\r\n\t\t\terror(\"ColorSchemePre was not invoked\")\r\n\t\tend\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`nvim -u NONE -u minimal.lua`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo error. I would expect the `ColorSchemePre` callback to be invoked.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo (`UIEnter` doesn't exist in Vim)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nNixOS 24.05 + NixOS unstable\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.13.2 (tmux 3.4)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnixpkgs",
